<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,219,243]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Description.</emphasis>
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[451,609,219,243]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="47.[113,152,1546,1565]" captionTargetBox="[117,1085,225,1393]" captionTargetId="figure-9@47.[113,1088,219,1394]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="Figs. 129–138. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view of: 129–130 – Colasposoma (Colasposoma) hajeki sp. nov.(Jholotype); 131–132 – Erythraella bicuspidata gen. et sp. nov. (J holotype); 133–134 – Macrocoma niedobovae sp. nov. (J holotype); 135–136 – Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov. (J holotype); 137–138 – M. hulai sp. nov. (J holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339808/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Figs. 135–136</figureCitation>
; body length of 
<typeStatus box="[792,885,219,243]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[894,980,220,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
, of 
<typeStatus box="[1024,1126,220,244]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">paratypes</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[151,279,252,276]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="2.3499999999999996" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.4 mm</quantity>
(JJ), 
<quantity box="[355,436,251,275]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount box="[452,471,245,276]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Body black with metallic reflections; head, pronotum and elytra dark with bronze metallic reflections; labrum black, mandibles dark brown to black, palpi dark brown; antennomere I blackish, II–VI reddish or partially darkened, antennomeres VII–XI dull, blackish; legs including tarsi black, with slightly metallic reflections. Slightly teneral specimen with antennae and legs reddish.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">
Frons (
<figureCitation box="[257,336,443,467]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) nearly flat in middle, without longitudinal median sulcus; pubescence of frons and clypeus relatively long, silvery, sometimes absent along median line; punctation strong, close; surface between punctures convex, shiny, narrower than diameter of puncture; clypeus not separated from frons, its distal border concave, V-shaped. Two apical maxillary palpomeres oblong, penultimate nearly two thirds of ultimate one in length, 1.5 times longer than wide. Antennomere I nearly 1.2 times longer than II and nearly 1.2 times as wide, feebly bent on outer side; antennomere II two times longer than wide; antennomere III one third shorter than II, one third longer than wide; antennomere IV shorter than III, subequal to V; antennomere VI the shortest; antennomeres VII–X dull, widened, VII subtriangular, nearly two times wider than VI, antennomeres VIII–X transverse; antennomere XI 1.2 times longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">
Pronotum as wide as long (1.4 × 
<quantity box="[524,604,796,820]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus box="[635,733,795,819]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">holotype</typeStatus>
); base as wide as distal border; lateral margin absent; surface with strong, close punctation; pubescence long, silvery (
<figureCitation box="[999,1078,827,851]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Scutellum subquadrate, sides and distal border nearly straight, with 2–4 relatively strong punctures bearing short silvery pubescence.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">
Hypomeron shiny, with strong and close punctation and long silvery pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1114,923,947]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
); distal border of prosternum regularly concave, continuous with that of hypomerae; notosternal suture nearly vanished; prosternum 1.5 times longer than wide between procoxae, nearly flat, strongly punctate, with long silvery pubescence. Mesoventrite short, slightly wider than prosternum between procoxae, its distal edge straight, surface punctured, with fine pubescence; mesepimera finely punctured, pubescent. Metaventrite incised along median line, with moderately strong punctures and moderately long silvery pubescence, distal border shortly incised medially; metacoxae nearly as spaced as mesocoxae; metanepisterna lightly tapering toward rear, nearly 4.5 times longer than wide, punctured and pubescent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">
Elytra 1.2–1.3 times longer than wide at humeri (1.4 × 
<quantity box="[775,857,1212,1236]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[933,1031,1211,1235]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">holotype</typeStatus>
); surface regularly convex, humeri distinct; sides subparallel from humeri up to half (J) or three fifths (
<specimenCount box="[160,179,1269,1300]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
) of their length, then regularly curved to apex; apices at slightly acute angle; punctation relatively strong, arranged in nearly regular rows alternated with lines of recumbent fine silvery setae (10 rows on each elytron, the tenth along lateral elytral margin) and lines of erected wider setae (10 rows on each elytron) (
<figureCitation box="[645,725,1371,1396]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
). Epipleura gradually tapering toward rear, relatively strongly punctured, finely pubescent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1127,219,1555]" pageId="30" pageNumber="479">Legs moderately long; femora with small median tooth, moderately swollen; tibiae nearly straight, with fine silvery pubescence. Pro– and mesotarsi slightly widened in males, with tarsomere I wider than tarsomere II. Claws bifid, with long, subparallel inner tooth, division starting near base of claw.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Dorsal side of abdomen sclerotized, dark in color, with some metallic reflections, pygidium fully covered by elytra; abdominal ventrites punctured and pubescent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" box="[144,445,283,308]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">
Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[312,441,283,308]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Figs. 90–91</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">
Spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation box="[341,419,315,340]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="43.[113,152,1518,1537]" captionTargetBox="[173,1022,225,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-9@43.[173,1029,219,1492]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figs. 90–97.Macrocoma bezdeki sp. nov.(90–91, 93, 96–97:J holotype; 92:J, Aloove vill. env.; 94–95:♀, Aloove vill. env.): 90 – aedeagus, apex, dorsal view; 91 – aedeagus, lateral view; 92 – tegmen; 93 – ventral sclerite of sternite IX; 94 – spermatheca; 95 – pronotum, lateral view; 96 – head; 97 – elytral punctation and pubescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339800/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
; coxites short, conical, sclerotized; spiculum ventrale relatively long and thin; vagina without any sclerotization.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="480" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,359,379,403]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zoia, 2012" authorityName="Zoia" authorityYear="2012" box="[363,574,381,404]" class="Bryopsida" family="Orthotrichaceae" genus="Macrocoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Orthotrichales" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="bezdeki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[363,574,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Macrocoma bezdeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[579,659,380,403]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a small species characterized by elytral pubescence with alternate rows of scale–like setae and thin setae. It is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zoia, 2012" authorityName="Zoia" authorityYear="2012" box="[932,1089,413,436]" class="Bryopsida" family="Orthotrichaceae" genus="Macrocoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Orthotrichales" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="niedobovae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[932,1089,413,436]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">M. niedobovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[113,195,444,467]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from which it differs mainly in its smaller size and more cylindrical, as long as wide pronotum. From 
<taxonomicName authority="Zoia, 2012" authorityName="Zoia" authorityYear="2012" box="[293,383,477,500]" class="Bryopsida" family="Orthotrichaceae" genus="Macrocoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Orthotrichales" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="hulai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[293,383,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">M. hulai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[389,471,476,499]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
it differs mainly in the absence of a small and flat tubercle on pronotal sides.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="480" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,241,540,564]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Etymology.</emphasis>
I am pleased to name this species after Jan Bezděk (Brno, 
<collectingCountry box="[844,1015,539,563]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
), a collector of the specimens studied and well known specialist in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[761,927,571,595]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
: Galerucinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,1089,219,660]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,398,603,627]" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Collection circumstances.</emphasis>
Specimens from Aloove were collected beating 
<taxonomicName authority="Balf." authorityName="Balf." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="socotranus">
<emphasis box="[895,1089,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="480">Croton socotranus</emphasis>
Balf.
</taxonomicName>
f. (J. Bezděk, pers. comm. 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
